{
  "texts": [
    "For example, combining molecular structure embeddings with image-based plating cues and environmental context (e.g., temperature, sound) allows AI to simulate real-world dining experiences with higher ecological validity.",
    "Such models could support innovations in virtual tasting, immersive product testing, and cross-modal flavor engineering.",
    "Generative AI is also poised to revolutionize sensory innovation.",
    "Techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs), variational autoencoders (VAEs), and diffusion models can learn latent distributions of molecular properties associated with taste and smell (Çoban 2023).",
    "These models enable the de novo design of flavor-active molecules and synthetic odorants with tunable perceptual effects."
  ]
}